*   **[Computational learning theory](/Computational_learning_theory):** The theoretical study of machine learning algorithms.
*   **[Empirical risk minimization](/Empirical_risk_minimization):** A principle for learning models by minimizing the error on the training data.
*   **[Occam learning](/Occam_learning):** The principle that simpler explanations are generally better.
*   **[PAC learning](/Probably_approximately_correct_learning):** A theoretical framework for analyzing the learnability of concepts.
*   **[Statistical learning](/Statistical_learning_theory):** A framework that views learning as a statistical inference problem.
*   **[VC theory](/Vapnik%E2%80%93Chervonenkis_theory):** A theory of statistical learning that provides bounds on the generalization error.
